# TDD Enforcement (Superpowers Workflow)

When working with test files, follow the RED-GREEN-REFACTOR cycle:

## RED Phase
- Write a failing test FIRST
- The test should describe the desired behavior
- Run the test to confirm it fails for the right reason

## GREEN Phase
- Write the MINIMUM code to make the test pass
- Don't optimize yet — just make it work
- Run the test to confirm it passes

## REFACTOR Phase
- Clean up the code while keeping tests green
- Remove duplication, improve naming
- Run all tests to confirm nothing broke

## Testing Pyramid
- **70% Unit tests** — fast, isolated, test one thing
- **20% Integration tests** — test component interactions
- **10% E2E tests** — test full user flows

## Rules
- Never commit code without tests
- Test the behavior, not the implementation
- One assertion per test (when practical)
- Use descriptive test names: `should [expected] when [condition]`
- Mock external dependencies, not internal modules

